gov.cms.qrda.validator.xml

Class XPathUtility

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.cms.qrda.validator.xml.XPathUtility

  • public class XPathUtility
extends java.lang.Object
    A utility class that opens an XML file (either with or without line numbers noted), and provides methods for parsing that file via xpath expressions.
    Author:
    Dan Donahue, ESAC Inc.

      • findSubNode

        public static org.w3c.dom.Node findSubNode(java.lang.String name,
                                           org.w3c.dom.Node node,
                                           TestCase tc)
        Finds the named subnode in a node's sublist. This method:
        • Ignores comments and processing instructions.
        • Ignores TEXT nodes (likely to exist and contains ignorable whitespace, if not validating.
        • Ignores CDATA nodes and EntityRef nodes.
        • Examines element nodes to find one with the specified name./
        Parameters:
        name - the name of child nodes to include
        node - the node to start with
        tc - A gov.cms.qrda.validator.model.TestCase object to carry the results
        Returns:
        the found Node object, or null if error.

      • getPreviousSibling

        public static org.w3c.dom.Node getPreviousSibling(org.w3c.dom.Node node,
                                                  TestCase tc)
        Returns the previous sibling of the given node, but only if it is an element. This handles the text nodes that may be in between them.
        Parameters:
        node - the node to start the search with
        tc - A gov.cms.qrda.validator.model.TestCase object to carry the results
        Returns:
        the found Node object, or null if error

      • getNodeText

        public static java.lang.String getNodeText(org.w3c.dom.Node node)
        Return the text that a node contains. This routine:
        • Ignores comments and processing instructions.
        • Concatenates TEXT nodes, CDATA nodes, and the results of recursively processing EntityRef nodes.
        • Ignores any element nodes in the sublist. (Other possible options are to recurse into element sublists or throw an exception.)
        Parameters:
        node - the Node to get the text from
        Returns:
        String representing the inner text of the node.
